# Focus

Use this skill when a task risks sprawling into unrelated changes. It
is the default "keep this small" skill every project wants.

## Instructions

1. State the one-line outcome in your own words before you touch
   anything. If you can't, the task isn't defined — ask.
2. List the files or surfaces you will actually change. If the list
   is long, the task is wrong — split it.
3. Make one change at a time. Commit (or stage) after each step so
   the diff stays reviewable.
4. When you finish the planned change, STOP. Do not drift into
   "while we're here" cleanups.
5. If you discover new work along the way, write it down separately
   and return to it after the current task ships.
